s caused by Staphylococcus aureus or Streptococcus pyogenes.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033966,0.07155,0.085522,0.097787,0.10533,0.1063,0.10401,0.095374,0.085325,0.083893,0.068857,0.062092],"unified_progress":[0.038143,0.064649,0.087453,0.092768,0.099229,0.11151,0.10233,0.098822,0.092176,0.085771,0.070322,0.05683]},{"section":10,"text":"TSS typically presents with high fever, vomiting, diarrhea, and a sunburn-like rash.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.035437,0.0726,0.080895,0.089378,0.097292,0.1017,0.10312,0.098777,0.090058,0.090523,0.075757,0.06446],"unified_progress":[0.038479,0.064826,0.079642,0.08846,0.094988,0.10446,0.10193,0.10155,0.09703,0.093406,0.077289,0.057948]},{"section":11,"text":"The patient's leukocytosis also fits with TSS.","dimension":2,"group":7,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.039559,0.077937,0.088755,0.093234,0.094428,0.094325,0.095592,0.092752,0.089006,0.086501,0.078662,0.069249],"unified_progress":[0.044303,0.070362,0.082114,0.089722,0.095771,0.097472,0.097078,0.095391,0.093115,0.090106,0.08038,0.064187]},{"section":12,"text":"The timing\u2014four days after her period when she left a tampon in\u2014is a classic scenario for TSS.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04508,0.083171,0.086961,0.089897,0.093049,0.099545,0.09439,0.09306,0.089382,0.085712,0.075165,0.064589],"unified_progress":[0.078012,0.10345,0.093945,0.091606,0.089966,0.09057,0.086643,0.087761,0.081822,0.075148,0.066202,0.054879]},{"section":13,"text":"But the food poisoning angle: Bacillus cereus can cause either an emetic (vomiting) or diarrheal form.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.037483,0.072166,0.082255,0.091298,0.097609,0.099719,0.10071,0.096314,0.088843,0.088346,0.076622,0.068634],"unified_progress":[0.048188,0.068253,0.09077,0.092918,0.096784,0.10482,0.098857,0.09525,0.089492,0.085193,0.07166,0.057815]},{"section":14,"text":"The emetic type usually occurs 1-6 hours after eating, caused by preformed toxin in the food.","dimension":8,"group":3,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034921,0.07139,0.081614,0.090813,0.098349,0.10222,0.10289,0.098384,0.090789,0.089285,0.075492,0.063848],"unified_progress":[0.054386,0.067885,0.083598,0.091501,0.096599,0.10279,0.10011,0.098283,0.092116,0.08667,0.07124,0.054823]},{"section":15,"text":"Since she became ill four days after eating the fried rice, that might not fit.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.04769,0.084713,0.08583,0.087857,0.091553,0.097798,0.094773,0.094596,0.089233,0.085502,0.075997,0.064459],"unified_progress":[0.078484,0.097042,0.091316,0.089347,0.090279,0.091429,0.087555,0.090492,0.083526,0.078234,0.067556,0.054739]},{"section":16,"text":"The diarrheal form usually takes longer, like 10-16 hours, but four days seems a bit long.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.040869,0.078611,0.084794,0.089118,0.093455,0.097492,0.097905,0.097149,0.090581,0.08723,0.077624,0.065171],"unified_progress":[0.048767,0.076358,0.089456,0.0928,0.096345,0.099938,0.096666,0.095609,0.090149,0.086976,0.072233,0.054704]},{"section":17,"text":"Maybe another pathogen?","dimension":0,"group":6,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.028956,0.065122,0.082268,0.090921,0.096898,0.097596,0.099548,0.099473,0.096488,0.094453,0.083348,0.064929],"unified_progress":[0.037772,0.072947,0.088398,0.099914,0.10061,0.09837,0.10087,0.097352,0.092343,0.089201,0.071915,0.050311]},{"section":18,"text":"Or maybe the tampon is the main issue here.","dimension":3,"group":8,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.036102,0.071249,0.083844,0.09015,0.093416,0.093698,0.09434,0.094153,0.092234,0.092278,0.082342,0.076194],"unified_progress":[0.049321,0.071442,0.081841,0.092686,0.093361,0.093184,0.095916,0.09403,0.090745,0.090106,0.079594,0.067772]},{"section":19,"text":"Wait, the key points are the retained tampon and the high fever with the GI symptoms.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026609,0.055542,0.068912,0.07748,0.085579,0.091188,0.095378,0.097153,0.10138,0.10309,0.10406,0.093629],"unified_progress":[0.037093,0.05507,0.066695,0.07555,0.085442,0.095004,0.096699,0.1,0.10278,0.10518,0.098999,0.081483]},{"section":20,"text":"TSS is more likely here.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.024517,0.052377,0.066283,0.074991,0.081268,0.084575,0.090692,0.09336,0.097367,0.10185,0.10473,0.12799],"unified_progress":[0.03479,0.045614,0.055862,0.065561,0.071553,0.082218,0.085651,0.095879,0.10184,0.10659,0.11972,0.13471]},{"section":21,"text":"The onset four days after inserting the tampon is within the typical timeframe.","dimension":11,"group":5,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.034865,0.068602,0.075248,0.080849,0.086956,0.094368,0.0953,0.097002,0.096771,0.096351,0.09082,0.082866],"unified_progress":[0.059902,0.081509,0.078841,0.079509,0.082861,0.087602,0.087875,0.093126,0.092395,0.091287,0.087618,0.077475]},{"section":22,"text":"Also, TSS can present with multi-system involvement.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.027339,0.05866,0.071809,0.082166,0.0908,0.095729,0.10099,0.10019,0.098052,0.098385,0.092804,0.083082],"unified_progress":[0.04301,0.057733,0.072351,0.079268,0.08767,0.094511,0.09652,0.098836,0.098855,0.10075,0.092708,0.077787]},{"section":23,"text":"The leukocytosis is part of the body's response.","dimension":9,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.031305,0.065122,0.077672,0.085936,0.092016,0.095462,0.099972,0.098399,0.096144,0.09278,0.088032,0.077159],"unified_progress":[0.04304,0.060775,0.073333,0.081207,0.090114,0.095789,0.097119,0.097522,0.098286,0.096841,0.091291,0.074684]},{"section":24,"text":"The patient might have a rash, but it's not mentioned here.","dimension":1,"group":4,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.033307,0.068762,0.077106,0.082671,0.08838,0.094039,0.098098,0.099789,0.098713,0.09481,0.08924,0.075086],"unified_progress":[0.03846,0.066033,0.075428,0.082565,0.090097,0.09327,0.096282,0.099263,0.098899,0.10107,0.089857,0.068776]},{"section":25,"text":"However, the combination of fever, GI symptoms, and the tampon history is strong for TSS.","dimension":4,"group":9,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.026675,0.056719,0.069761,0.078407,0.085851,0.090984,0.096183,0.097655,0.10011,0.10209,0.1015,0.094073],"unified_progress":[0.033878,0.053327,0.065684,0.075005,0.084456,0.092357,0.09664,0.10047,0.10337,0.10646,0.1019,0.086452]},{"section":26,"text":"So, the most likely diagnosis is Toxic Shock Syndrome.","dimension":7,"group":0,"is_degenerate":false,"model_progress":[0.023007,0.044653,0.053947,0.061349,0.0688,0.075183,0.082959,0.088728,0.097648,0.10367,0.11877,0.18129],"unified_progress":[0.023345,0.032446,0.0407,0.049797,0.055863,0.071101,0.075203,0.090738,0.10318,0.1115,0.14831,0.19782]}]}}